Package gw.api.json

Class JsonObject

java.lang.Object
gw.api.json.JsonObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
Map<String,Object>
public class JsonObject extends Object implements Map<String,Object>
A JsonObject is a Map of values, suitable for serializing out as JSON or XML, either with or without an associated JSON schema definition. The values in a JsonObject are Java types rather than just the JSON primitive types, i.e. the values can be BigDecimals, Dates, or TypeKeys, among other options. Lists are used to represent JSON arrays, and nested objects are represented with other JsonObject instances.

Both serialization and deserialization can be done either with or without an associated schema. In the case of deserialization, if a schema is supplied, the input data will be validated against that schema and property values will be deserialized into Java types based on the types specified in the schema. If a schema is not supplied, deserialization will only deserialize into basic Java types (String, Boolean, Double, List, or JsonObject).

In the case of serialization, if a schema is supplied, the JsonObject will be validated against the schema, and the schema property types will be used to determine the output formatting. If no schema is supplied, no validation will happen, and default output mappings will be used for Java types.
